OL,6,FYet he also rejected the idea he was
OL,7,Fseparating himself from the Tory Party
OL,8,Fnationally - "I'm standing as a
OL,9,FConservative candidate, if I was
OL,10,Fseparating myself I wouldn't be doing
OL,11,Fthat", he said.
OL,13,FMany voters did tell ITV News they
OL,14,Fdisliked the Tory Government, but said
OL,15,Fthey would still vote for Mr Houchen,
OL,16,Freferring to him fondly as "Ben".
