OL,6,F"I am voting for Ben because I do
OL,7,Fthink he does a good job and he's
OL,8,Fdelivered on what he's promised," she
OL,9,Fsaid.
OL,11,FThe man hoping to beat Mr Houchen is
OL,12,FLabour councillor Chris McEwan, who
OL,13,Finsists voters want a change from the
OL,14,FTories: "It's a cliche to say 'time
OL,15,Ffor change' but the term has been used
OL,16,Fwith me by local people many times".
OL,18,F"Help us struggle less," one business
OL,19,Fowner in Tees Valley said as he
OL,20,Fhighlighted what matters for him in
OL,21,Flocal politicians
