OL,6,FThursday marks his third time running
OL,7,Ffor mayor of the West Midlands, which
OL,8,Fincludes Birmingham, Wolverhampton and
OL,9,FCoventry, and is a region boasting a
OL,10,Fmix of red and blue wall voters
OL,11,Fspanning across urban and rural areas.
OL,13,FIn September, Mr Street made national
OL,14,Fheadlines and was hailed locally when
OL,15,Fhe almost quit the party over HS2. He
OL,16,Fclashed publicly with the prime
OL,17,Fminister following the announcement
OL,18,Fthe government was scrapping the high-
OL,19,Fspeed rail line from Birmingham to
OL,20,FManchester.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G    G15/22
