OL,6,FShe doesn't know who she'll vote for
OL,7,Fbut she's certain it won't be Mr
OL,8,FStreet. "I just don't think he
OL,9,Funderstands the communities," she
OL,10,Fsays. "Walk the walk that we have to
OL,11,Fwalk. Talk to your communities."
OL,13,FMr Street defended his track record,
OL,14,Ftelling ITV News: "I would say there's
OL,15,Fhuge disappointment across city about
OL,16,Fwhat's happened, but I actually don't
OL,17,Frecognise what you say that I'm
OL,18,Fpersonally responsible for that.
